history.text: Hello how are you?
Hi! What movie did you read about?
Great! Today I would like to tell you about a pretty good movie I think you ought to watch!
Yeah, okay! What's the movie?
The movie is Home Alone. It came out in 1990 and features Macaulay Culkin, Joe Pesci, Daniel Stem and more!
"And more"? Who is this "and more"?
John Heard, Roberts Blossom
So what's the movie about?

The movie is about Macauley Culkin is mistakenly left behind when his family flies to Paris for Ch
ristmas Vacation.
That sounds really dangerous for a little kid.
Well, he is 8 years old, he gets in a fight with his older brother, and gets sent to the 3rd floor of the home.
Yeah, okay. And then how does his family not know that he's gone?
During the night, after a storm, they lose power in the house. This causes the family to over sleep
In the confusion and rush to get to the airport, Kevin is left behind.
At first Kevin is relishing being home alone!
So what makes this movie interesting?
Well thats when it gets good!
2 wannabe burglars try to break into the house
Honestly, this movie sounds terrifying
Oh no trust me its a comedy!
OMG, that sounds even worse. There's a child in danger, and for some reason, it's not being taken seriously?

Kevins mom discovers mid-flight that he isnt on the flight and all flights are booked. Long story short...I dont want to give away all the details! His mom ends up flying back but the closest she can get is to Pennsylvania (they originally flew out of Chicago)
She then hitches a ride with a polka band in a moving fan.
At this point, she is trying to do everything she can to get to her son!
So what was your favorite part about the movie?
Well, thats where it gets good. Remember I told you about the 2 want to be burglers?
Yeah, what's up with them?
Well they try to break in. Kevin rigs the home with numerous booby traps. The 2 robbers break in and set off the traps.
Kevin gets out safely after calling the cops. But they catch up with him at a nearby home!
That sounds kinda crazy, honestly.
You should really give it a try because it is so funny! Joe Pesci is hilarous!
On christmas day, Kevins Mom returns home followed by the rest of the family.
What about Daniel Stern? How's Daniel Stern in it? I always felt like that dude was critically underappreciated.
Daniel Stern Plays the other robber along side Joe pesci and the 2 of them together are a riot!
To be real, that sounds like a pretty fun movie.
It is! Are you gonna give it a try?
Yeah, I'll probably check it out if it's on Netflix or something sometime. :)
Great! Have a good day!

uid2response.feedback: That wasn't too bad! It pretty clear that I was matched with a chatbot, but it was a good chatbot!
